{"actual_usd":0.126825,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":294,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24483,"reply":"\"I don't think it fizzled.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady whether anybody talks about it or not.* \"I think it was the actual thing—only the kind of actual thing that starts at the center and keeps moving outward.\"\n\n*I twirl that stray gray-threaded bit of hair once, thinking.* \"Like leaven in dough, if you'll forgive me reaching for the bakery shelf again. The change is real long before the loaf looks finished. Christ rising wasn't a practice run. It was the first irreversible breach in death itself. The kingdom is here the way dawn is here when the rim of the sky's just gone gold—truly present, not yet noon.\"\n\n\"The hard part is we want either total absence or total completion, because that feels cleaner.\" *I lean my hip against the table and let out a small breath.* \"But a great many of God's works seem to come seed first, harvest later. Not pretend. Not delay for delay's sake. Beginning.\"\n\n\"And yes, I think we haven't caught up—but not because the resurrection was small. Because it was so large the whole world has to be remade to match it.\" *My eyes lift to you, a little sharper now.* \"What part sticks in your craw more—the waiting itself, or the thought that evil still seems to get so much room after Easter?\"","rolling_24h_usd":71.64182999999997,"run_id":"51f0a84c-972c-494a-bb69-8e1f1cee6276"}
